Android-SDK is a software development kit that are used to secondary development of printer, which is provided for customers. It uses Bluetooth communication protocol, and intended to be used application development of Android smart device that have BLUETOOTH interface, such as HTC, Motorola, Samsung and other brands of mobile phones and Android system Tablet. This SDK is basis on the ESC/POS command standard, printer with Bluetooth function are suitable for the printing of the system device. Typical application of Bluetooth phones and portable printer constitutes mobile printing Terminal. That is widely used in the areas of mobile printing requirements.
